item.description:
@F-0-N-Z-Y wrote:

[quote=“stormcutter, post:1, topic:200256”]K i have a small problem, when i add regular stuff to my client.java, save then compile, it works. BUt for some reason, now when i add safezones it isnt working! i compile then restart but still its not safe!!!

|| (absX >= 3217 && absX <= 3233 && absY >= 3222 && absY <= 3212)

isnt this right to make part of lumby safe???

wats wrong![/quote]

to make a safe zone, follow these steps.

|| (absX >= 3217 && absX <= 3233 && absY >= 3222 && absY <= 3212)
(absx >= north west (X co-ordinate)
(absx <= north east (x co-ordinate)
(absy >= south east (y co-ordinate)
(absy <= same as the North East (but the Y co-ordinate)

----n
–w--e
----s

so like
3141, 3143-NW--------------------------------NE-3147, 3143
| |
| |
3141, 3140–SW-------------------------------SE-3147, 3140

          the safe area for this would be:

|| (absX >= 3141 && absX <= 3147 && absY >= 3140 && absY <= 3143)

if you understand this, you should have no problems.

also, here is a small explanation of the symbols.
(smaller number should come first)

|| (absX >= 3217 && absX <= 3233 && absY >= 3222 && absY <= 3212)

the
absX >= 3217 && absX <= 3233
that means, any co-ordinates between 3217 and 3233 on the X axis (west to east)

the
absY >= 3222 && absY <= 3212
means any co-ordinate between 3222 and 3212 on the Y co-ordinate (north to south)

there is a problem on the Y co-ordinate, because the first number is larger than the second.

it should be:
absY >= 3212 && absY <= 3222

(that might be the problem that you had.
